    "Yi represents the i-th highest pixel value.",
    "F(Avg-TopK) represents the average of the k highest items.",
    "Figure 4 shows the operations for K = 3 in Avg-TopK pooling operation with a filter size of 3 × 3 from 6 × 6 pixel input.",
    "Both the Avg-TopK method and the Avg pooling method aim to address the drawbacks of the Max pooling and Average pooling methods.",
    "In the Avg pooling method, both highly representative values and minimally representative values are treated equally."
